Cell.Text: Dragonborn, I see you have not returned with any of my friends in tow. Were the people in the town of any help?
Werewolves! No wonder nobody travels to these islands. You look exhausted. Were you bitten? Are you hurt?

Node.Caption: igmeBloodMoon_stage2_sigrid0: Werewolves overran the town. I was lucky to escape.

Cell.Text: I'm glad to hear it. If the Dragonborn could not return, what chance would we stand? | I took a closer look at the markings around the camp, hoping to determine who... or what attacked us. | The markings around the camp are far too large to be human, or even werewolf. They reminded me of bear claws, really... | ... but there aren't any bears on this island.

Node.Caption: igmeBloodMoon_stage2_sigrid4: I made it out with a few scratches, but I'm fine.

Cell.Text: Perhaps... though, it seems unlikely. | It's getting late. Get some well-deserved rest and we can plan another course of action in the morning. | Havgrir will keep the fire stoked throughout the night. The temperature in this part of the world plummets after sundown.

Node.Caption: igmeBloodMoon_stage2_sigrid10: See you in the morning, Sigrid.

Node.Caption: igmeBloodMoon_stage2_sigrid9: It was a Werebear, for sure.

Cell.Text: Cursed? This whole island is cursed, as far as I can tell!

Node.Caption: igmeBloodMoon_stage2_sigrid3: Tons, if you like having your neck clawed at in the middle of the night.
